transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Diego.

Speaker 2: Hello Diego.

Speaker 1: How are we doing, sir? All right. I just got another—

Speaker 2: Order of—

Speaker 1: Sedona Phil.

Speaker 2: Today, and I got an order about a month ago, so I'd rather you didn't ship me any more—

Speaker 1: Medications until I call and ask for it.

Speaker 2: So I'm on there. Mr. William Barr, right?

Speaker 1: Correct. Yeah, I want to tell the pharmacy to stop the initial writing that I see here, which is 10 tablets every 30 days.

Speaker 2: So that being said, you're just gonna call to reorder as needed?

Speaker 1: They're gonna pause you, I think, up to half a year, and you can call, and if you just maintain to refill a year—

Speaker 2: You're always gonna get the price that you're getting right now. Only thing is we're gonna stop the monthly. Okay?

Speaker 1: Yeah, just stop the monthly for now. I'll call you when I need more.

Speaker 2: Okay, I'll do that for you.

Speaker 1: I'm gonna pause your prescription just to lock your price in as well, so you don't pay a higher price when you reorder.

Speaker 2: What do I pay for?

Speaker 1: $63.95.

Speaker 2: What's that?

Speaker 1: $63.95, so there's six bucks a piece, huh?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I mean the more you get is a little better. Usually you can get 25 pills, you know.

Speaker 1: You save a little more, but you know, it's based on the monthly budget that you can allow.

Speaker 2: Yeah, well I stopped the monthly right now, so you'd be good.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Yeah, my girl and I are in our 70s. We don't—we're not that busy.

Speaker 1: I'm sorry, three times a week?

Speaker 2: Yeah, two to three. Yeah, that's pretty good.

Speaker 1: Well, for considering our age it is, you know.

Speaker 2: It wouldn't be good if we were in our 20s, but oh—

Speaker 1: Wow, but it's just seven days during the week. So that's at least half of the week. That's not bad.

Speaker 2: Well, thanks.

Speaker 1: Don't automatically send them to me because I don't—I don't consume them that fast.

Speaker 2: Yeah, everything will be paused for half a year, so you can reorder a monthly stop.

Speaker 1: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 2: You're welcome.
